  "prompt": "What is the difference between Gmail and email?",
  "response": "Gmail is a specific email service provided by Google, while email (electronic mail) is a broader communication method. Here are the key differences:\n\nEmail (General):\n- A communication method for sending digital messages\n- Can be used through various providers and platforms\n- A general technology that allows message exchange via internet\n- Can be accessed through different email services\n\nGmail:\n- A specific email service created by Google\n- Free email platform with certain features and storage\n- Includes @gmail.com email addresses\n- Offers specific tools like spam filtering, large storage, and integration with Google services\n- One of many email service providers (like Outlook, Yahoo Mail, etc.)\n\nIn simple terms, Gmail is a type of email service, while email is the overall method of digital communication.",
